      "deeperQuestionText": "How is it possible for a short, thin copper wire and a long, thick copper wire to have the exact same total resistance?",
      "deeperAnswerGuidance": [
        "Resistance depends on multiple physical factors",
        "Dimensions like length and area can balance each other out",
        "The resistivity is the same but the dimensions differ",
        "Total resistance is the result of resistivity, length, and area combined"
      ],
      "deeperSourceTeachingPointIds": [
        "TP3",
        "TP4"
      ],
      "hint": "Think about how the different physical dimensions of the wires might offset one another."
    },
    {
